  <steps>
    <step num="0">Peel and chop the potatoes very finely. </step>
    <step num="1">Place in a bowl, cover with cold water, and leave until ready to fry. </step>
    <step num="2">To make the batter, mix the chickpea flour, turmeric, chili powder, pepper, salt bicarbonate of soda, chillies, and coriander. </step>
    <step num="3">Gradually add the water while whisking to form a smooth batter. </step>
    <step num="4">Heat a pot of oil to 160˚C (320°F). </step>
    <step num="5">Drain the potato slices and dip in the batter. </step>
    <step num="6">Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown (around 3-4 minutes). </step>
    <step num="7">Serve with spicy ketchup. </step>
    <step num="8">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
